Create New Migration (Add Image Column)

Run:

php artisan make:migration add_image_to_users_table --table=users

Open the created migration file.

Example:

database/migrations/xxxx_add_image_to_users_table.php

Edit it like this:

use Illuminate\Database\Migrations\Migration;
use Illuminate\Database\Schema\Blueprint;
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Schema;

return new class extends Migration
{
    public function up()
    {
        Schema::table('users', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->string('image')->nullable()->after('mobile');
        });
    }

    public function down()
    {
        Schema::table('users', function (Blueprint $table) {
            $table->dropColumn('image');
        });
    }
};


2. Run Migration


php artisan migrate

Now users table becomes

| id | name | email | mobile | image | password | status |



